    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{3x^{2}y^{2}-xy-4}{-5xy-3-2x^{2}y^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3xy-4}{2xy+3}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{3x^{2}y^{2}-xy-4}{-5xy-3-2x^{2}y^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{\left(3xy-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(xy+1\right)}}{{-2x^{2}y^{2}-5xy-3}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(3xy-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(xy+1\right)}}{{-\left(2x^{2}y^{2}+5xy+3\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(3xy-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(xy+1\right)}}{{-\left(2xy+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(xy+1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{3xy-4}{2xy+3}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
